description:
&lt;p&gt;When you offer your compassion, commitment and skills as a hospital volunteer, you’re helping to improve a patient’s experience. There are many benefits to volunteering, including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;learning new skills and knowledge&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;contributing to other people’s wellbeing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;personal achievement, increased confidence and self-esteem&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;community involvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;meeting new people and reducing isolation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Patient Experience Department is offering an opportunity to join the growing team of Meet and Greet volunteers who will be situated at the various entrances in the RD&amp;E Hospital (Wonford) and Community Hospital sites. You will act as the first point of contact with the public to ensure infection, prevention and control (IPC) guidance is being followed such as using hand gel and providing relevant personal protective equipment (PPE) in line with COVID-19 guidelines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Other tasks may include the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Signposting patients and visitor to various wards and out-patient areas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dealing with general patient enquiries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Receive patient property from relatives while visiting is restricted.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Transport patients by wheelchair to various departments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collect wheelchairs where available and returning them to Main Reception to help ensure there is a continuous supply of wheelchairs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to be able to commit to a minimum of 3½ hours’ volunteering every week. Opportunities are available between 8am-6pm including weekends.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are friendly, welcoming and proactive, with good communication skills and the ability to remain calm and put people at their ease then please get in touch.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Brenda Leaman, Patient Experience Lead on 01392 406050.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our vision is to provide safe, high quality seamless services delivered with courtesy and respect. To achieve our vision we expect all our staff and volunteers to uphold our Trust values which are:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Honesty, Openness &amp; Integrity&lt;br /&gt;Fairness&lt;br /&gt;Inclusion &amp; Collaboration&lt;br /&gt;Respect &amp; Dignity&lt;/p&gt;
